# Copy to deploy/.env and fill in.
# Your domain (also the WebSocket Origin allowlist). For the DEFAULT `tls internal` Caddy setup a
# LAN-only name is fine; for zero-device-install public certs use a name on an API-accessible DNS
# provider for Let's Encrypt DNS-01.
MP_DOMAIN=hub.home.example.com
# API token for your DNS provider (ONLY needed for the DNS-01 upgrade path; see deploy/Caddyfile).
MP_DNS_TOKEN=changeme
# REQUIRED shared secret gating the control channel (WebSocket + state-changing /api routes). The
# hub REFUSES TO START on a real network interface with this empty, because an open control plane
# lets anyone on the LAN/tailnet start/stop/max-volume the speakers. Generate one:
#   openssl rand -hex 24
# Then open the apps with the token in the URL fragment once (persists to the device):
#   https://hub.home.example.com/controller/#t=YOUR_TOKEN
MP_TOKEN=
# Escape hatch: set to 1 to intentionally run WITHOUT a token on a trusted LAN (not recommended).
MP_ALLOW_OPEN=
